<controls:ChildWindow x:Class="TheS.Casinova.Colors.Views.HowToPlayWindow"
           xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation" 
           xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml" 
           xmlns:controls="clr-namespace:System.Windows.Controls;assembly=System.Windows.Controls"
           Width="600" Height="400" 
           Title="How to play." FontSize="21.333">
    <Grid x:Name="LayoutRoot" Margin="2">
        <Grid.RowDefinitions>
            <RowDefinition />
            <RowDefinition Height="Auto" />
        </Grid.RowDefinitions>

        <Button x:Name="CloseButton" Content="Close" Click="CloseButton_Click" Width="75" Height="23" HorizontalAlignment="Right" Margin="0,12,0,0" Grid.Row="1" FontSize="11" />
        <Grid>
        	<RichTextBox Margin="0" FontSize="11" HorizontalScrollBarVisibility="Visible" IsReadOnly="True">
        		<Paragraph>
        			<Run Text="Game: Colors"
        			FontWeight="Bold"
					FontSize="12"></Run>
					<LineBreak/><LineBreak/>
					<Run Text="Standard Rules"
        			FontWeight="Bold"></Run>
					<LineBreak/>
- Each game period lasts 15 minutes<LineBreak/>
- Each player may place any amount of bet on either Black, White, or Draw (Player also may choose to place bets on some or all of them)<LineBreak/>
- Each dollar bet in "Black" will increase the value of Black by one.<LineBreak/>
- Each dollar bet in "White" will increase the value of White by one.<LineBreak/>
- Any amount bet in "Draw" will not effect the value of either Black or White.<LineBreak/>
- Any Player may pay 1 dollar to see the "current status" of bets.<LineBreak/>
- The "current status" will only show whether "Black is winning", "White is winning", or "Draw".  It will not display the value of either Black or White.<LineBreak/>
- The screen will only display the current status.  It will not be updated until a player pays to update it.  An update can be ordered for 50 cents.<LineBreak/>
<LineBreak/>
<Run Text="Winners" FontWeight="Bold"/>
<LineBreak/>
- Players who bet on Black will win, if the value of Black is lower than the value of White at the end of the game.<LineBreak/>
- Players who bet on White will win, if the value of White is lower than the value of Black at the end of the game.<LineBreak/>
- Players who bet on Draw will win, if the value of Black and White are exactly the same at the end of the game.<LineBreak/>
<LineBreak/><Run Text="Payouts" FontWeight="Bold"/>
<LineBreak/>
- If Black wins, 1:2<LineBreak/>
- If White wins, 1:2.<LineBreak/>
- If Draw wins, 1:10.<LineBreak/>
				</Paragraph>     	
			</RichTextBox>
        </Grid>
    </Grid>
</controls:ChildWindow>